modules.description: Reads data from a Unix file descriptor into a buffer for parsing. Uses `Reparse.input` to manage incremental reading and tracking of input positions. Useful for parsing structured data from files or sockets without loading the entire content into memory.

Reads data incrementally from Unix file descriptors using a buffer, supporting efficient parsing of structured data from files or sockets. Tracks input positions to enable precise error reporting and resumption of parsing. Designed for use cases like log file analysis or network protocol parsing where memory efficiency and incremental processing are critical.
